article.headline: Keisha Hampton surpasses 1,000 points as DePaul beats Northern Illinois
article.linkText: Hampton surpasses 1,000 points as DePaul wins
article.story:
CHICAGO --  Keisha Hampton scored 11 points to eclipse 1,000 for her career and help DePaul (No. 24 AP) to a 72-52 win over Northern Illinois on Saturday.

Hampton, a 6-2 junior forward, broke a 9-9 tie early in the game with a 3-pointer that kicked off a decisive 20-4 run. She became the 25th player in school history to reach 1,000 points when she hit a free throw late in the game.

Sam Quigley had 13 points, Deanna Ortiz had 12 on four 3-pointers, and Felicia Chester and Katherine Harry each added 10 for DePaul (11-1), which has won eight straight and improved to 7-0 at McGrath Arena.

Kim Davis scored 18 points for the Huskies (5-4) and Marke Freeman added 11.
